<h1>Barton-McCombie Reaction<br>Barton Deoxygenation</h1>
<p><img src="barton7.gif" width="349" height="76"></p>
<p>A method for the deoxygenation of alcohols. The alcohol is first converted to the 
thiocarbonyl derivative, and is then treated with
<a href="../chemicals/reductions/tributyltinhydride-tributylstannane.shtm">Bu<sub>3</sub>SnH</a>. Once the radical chain has been initiated, attack 
on the Bu<sub>3</sub>Sn carrier by sulphur initiates a decomposition 
yielding the alkyl radical, for which Bu<sub>3</sub>SnH serves as 
hydrogen radical (H·) donor. The driving force for the reaction is the 
formation of the very stable S-Sn bonds.</p>
<hr>
